de.lmu.ifi.dbs.elki.utilities.datastructures.heap

Class ComparableMinHeap<K extends Comparable<K>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.lmu.ifi.dbs.elki.utilities.datastructures.heap.AbstractHeap
      • de.lmu.ifi.dbs.elki.utilities.datastructures.heap.ObjectHeap<K>
        • de.lmu.ifi.dbs.elki.utilities.datastructures.heap.ComparableMinHeap<K>

  • public class ComparableMinHeap<K extends Comparable<K>>
extends ObjectHeap<K>
    Basic in-memory heap structure. This heap is built lazily: if you first add many elements, then poll the heap, it will be bulk-loaded in O(n) instead of iteratively built in O(n log n). This is implemented via a simple validTo counter.
